I'm so sorry
I misjudged you, Mom.

246
00:14:27,466 --> 00:14:29,934
You had to leave
to protect your family.

247
00:14:30,035 --> 00:14:33,835
- How did you survive?
- Oh, I had help from my friends in the underground.

248
00:14:33,939 --> 00:14:37,340
Jerry Rubin gave me a job marketing
his line of health shakes...

249
00:14:37,443 --> 00:14:39,673
I proofread
Bobby Seale's cookbook...

250
00:14:39,778 --> 00:14:42,679
and I ran credit checks
at Tom Hayden's Porsche dealership.

251
00:14:42,781 --> 00:14:46,012
Wait a minute.
There's one thing I don't understand.

252
00:14:46,118 --> 00:14:49,349
In all those years, why didn't you
ever try to contact me?

253
00:14:49,455 --> 00:14:52,686
But I did. I sent you
a care package every week.

254
00:14:52,791 --> 00:14:55,988
Oh, come on, Mom. We use that same line
on the kids when they're at camp.

255
00:14:56,095 --> 00:14:58,723
But I did. I really did.
I'll prove it to you.

256
00:15:02,201 --> 00:15:04,965
- Any undelivered mail for HomerJ. Simpson?
- No.

257
00:15:05,070 --> 00:15:06,970
Oh, wait. This.

258
00:15:07,072 --> 00:15:09,870
That's what happens when you don't
tip your letter carrier at Christmas.

259
00:15:09,975 --> 00:15:13,741
Yes, I'd like to send this letter to
the Prussian consulate in Siam by aeromail.

260
00:15:13,846 --> 00:15:15,939
Am I too late
for the 4:30 autogiro?

261
